str2: However, nevertheless, but, except that, yet. From pleion; moreover, i.e. Albeit, save that, rather, yet.
To walk in, walk by. From a derivative of steicho; to march in rank, i.e. to conform to virtue and piety.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: Apparently a primary verb; to be beforehand, i.e. Anticipate or precede; by extension, to have arrived at.
